\begin_layout Section*
Q1.
 Recursive problem 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The recursive problem can be stated as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
v(s,a) & = & \underset{a'\in\Gamma(s,a)}{\text{max}}\left\{ \frac{\left(y(s)+a-qa'\right)^{1-\sigma}}{1-\sigma}+\beta\mathbb{E}_{s'|s}\left[v(s',a')\right]\right\} 
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

 by given budget constraint 
\begin_inset Formula $c=y(s)+a-qa'$
\end_inset

 and asssets bound 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{t+1}\ge\underline{a}$
\end_inset

.
 The state variables are 
\begin_inset Formula $s=\left\{ e,u\right\} $
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $a=\left\{ \underline{a},\bar{a}\right\} $
\end_inset

 i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\underline{a}=-2$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{a}=5$
\end_inset

 in homework, the control variable is 
\begin_inset Formula $a'$
\end_inset

 from 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma(s,a)=\left\{ a'\text{: }\underline{a}\le a'\le\frac{y(s)+a}{q}\right\} $
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

